title: Furniture of Williamsburg and eastern Virginia, 1710-1790
description:
Furniture of Williamsburg and Eastern Virginia, 1710-1790 by Wallace B Gusler
English | 1979 | 0917046056 | 222 Pages | PDF | 102 MB

A fascinating and readable analysis of the importance of the several Williamsburg cabinet making shops and the role they played in the furnishing of homes of eastern Virginia. Williamsburg was an important center of influence in the decorative arts, as it was in other areas. The photography is splendid as is the accompanying piece-by-piece furniture analysis
